2.4.1 The Strategy Plane
------------------------

The same strategic concerns come into play for both
functionality-oriented products and information-oriented resources.
*User needs* are the goals for the site that come from outside our
organization—specifically from the people who will use our site.  We
must understand what our audience wants from us and how that fits in
with other goals they have.

   Balanced against user needs are our own objectives for the site.
These *product objectives* can be business goals (“Make $1 million in
sales over the Web this year”) or other kinds of goals (“Inform voters
about the candidates in the next election”).  In Chapter 3 we will go
into more detail about these elements.


